:: CluePoint_JamesDean_SHARED:SVitruviusSnippet
/* --------------------------------------------------------------------- */\
/* - Vitruvius                                                         - */\
/* --------------------------------------------------------------------- */\
"There's not much to say. Vitruvius is an engineer who was working on the STORM program. Marlon thought he was acting suspiciously, and he wanted me to reassign him to a different program, but I honestly didn't think there was an issue."

"What was he suspicious about?"

"Well, he made a lot of visits to the French Ambassador."

"To <strong>Napolean</strong>?"

"Yeah. Marlon was pretty suspicious, especially given that Napolean is pretty important and Vitruvius, no offense to him, is just a engineer. A talented one, but still not very important. He has a good explanation, but it's his own business." He grins. "You can ask him about it if you like, but I'm not telling. Trust me that it's completely unrelated to possible corporate espionage. Besides, if he were doing espionage with the French, I imagine he'd try and keep the meetings a secret, which he definitely didn't do."

"Did he talk about the visits a lot?"

"Well, no, he didn't go out shouting to the world, but his co-workers knew. He was pretty popular, too. They were sad to see him go."

"Sad to see him go? Was he fired?"

"No, no, sorry, bad choice of words. I reassigned him. <strong>General Labienus</strong> followed the police investigation and didn't find his explanation credible, so he asked me to take him off the project and, since Labienus is the man in charge of the program, I had to." He shrugs. "It's a shame, but it's not career-threatening or anything. He seemed disappointed, but he took it in stride. I can get you his contact info, if you like."

"Yes, that'd be very helpful."

